{
  "texts": [
    "Spatial weight of the slowest-decaying mode (modelocalization diagnostic): grouping Majorana components per site yields site-resolved weights.Numerics use dense diagonalization of 2L × 2L matrices for X (possible for the sizes analyzed here) and averaging over a small number of ϕ realizations where indicated.",
    "We present rapidity linecuts κ(λ) for representative placements and t N values, finite-size scaling and spectral diagnostics for selected λ's (one in the delocalized-like regime and one in the localized-like regime), and slowmode spatial profiles.",
    "All data use periodic boundary conditions.A.",
    "Rapidity linecuts: dependence on λ and tN Figure 1 shows linecuts of κ vs λ for t N ∈ {0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0, 1.5} and the placement patterns that give nonzero gaps in our scans: uniform ('all'), single localized dissipator ('one-site'), and two localized dissipators ('two-site').",
    "The main trends are:• Uniform ('all'): large rapidity gaps (order 10 -1 in our units) and only weak dependence on λ. Dissipative channels cover the lattice so localization does not drastically reduce overlap with dissipators.• One-site / Two-site: much smaller gaps that shrink rapidly as λ increases."
  ]
}